Compute all the unnormalized Legendre polynomials.

Usage
-----
p = PLegendre (lmax, z)

Returns
-------
p : float, dimension (lmax+1)
    An array of unnormalized Legendre polynomials up to degree lmax. Degree l
    corresponds to array index l.

Parameters
----------
lmax : integer
    The maximum degree of the Legendre polynomials to be computed.
z : float
    The argument of the Legendre polynomial.

Description
-----------
PLegendre will calculate all of the unnormalized Legendre polynomials up to
degree lmax for a given argument. These are calculated using a standard three-
term recursion formula. The integral of the Legendre polynomials over the
interval [-1, 1] is 2/(2l+1).
